A total of seven out of 15 people injured in Tuesdayâ€™s school bus accident and rushed to Ligula Regional Referral Hospital in Mtwara have been referred to other hospitals for further medical treatments. Three of them have been referred to Muhimbili National Hospital (MNH) in Dar es Salaam while four others have been transported to Ndanda Hospital after sustaining serious injuries in different parts of their bodies. "Out of those 15 survivors, five people were referred to other hospitals yesterday. The number increased to seven this morning," acting Ligula Referral Regional Hospital acting Doctor in-charge, Dr Clemence Haule. He said the remaining eight are doing well and their condition is improving. On Tuesday a single-vehicle crash, involving a school bus, claimed 10 innocent lives on the spot. The death toll rose to thirteen after three more pupils died while receiving treatment at the Ligula Regional Referral Hospital.